column41: Pf3k is a global collaboration using the latest sequencing technologies to provide a high-resolution view of natural variation in the malaria parasite Plasmodium falciparum. The Project is led by researchers at the Broad Institute%2C the University of Oxford and the Wellcome Trust Sanger Institute. https%3A%2F%2Fwww.malariagen.net%2Fprojects%2Fparasite%2Fpf3k%0AThis data is part of a pre-publication release. For information on the proper use of pre-publication data shared by the Wellcome Trust Sanger Institute (including details of any publication moratoria)%2C please see http%3A%2F%2Fwww.sanger.ac.uk%2Fdatasharing%2F
column46: Comprehensive analysis of genome variation in 3%2C000 Plasmodium falciparum samples representing the major malaria endemic regions of the world
